# 1.0 INTRODUCTION 

## 1.1 Purpose 

> The purpose of this document is to enable users to easily identify the
> external source system of financial postings directly within the SAP
> cost center line-item report (KSB1). Currently, this information is
> only accessible by navigating into individual document headers, which
> is time-consuming and inefficient.
>
> Providing direct visibility into the external source identifier will
> reduce reconciliation effort, improve traceability, and allow
> stakeholders to more efficiently reconcile SAP postings with external
> source systems.

# 2.0 PROJECT OVERVIEW 

## 2.1 Objectives 

-   **Specific:** Provide visibility into external source system
    identifiers within the KSB1 report to support financial
    reconciliation.

-   **Measurable:** Enable users to reconcile SAP postings without
    drilling into individual document headers.

-   **Attainable:** Business need can be met using information already
    available in SAP postings.

-   **Realistic:** Business needs can be met using data already present
    in SAP financial documents.

-   **Time-bound:** Deliver reporting visibility by the end of Q4
    FY2025.

## 2.2 Assumptions 

> External source identifiers are consistently populated in SAP document
> headers for relevant postings. Users have the required authorization
> to view cost center line items and related information.

## 2.3 Constraints 

> The reporting change must not degrade report performance or user
> experience. The change must remain compatible with existing SAP
> reporting structures.

## 2.4 Risks 

> If external source identifiers are inconsistently populated,
> reconciliation accuracy may be impacted.
>
> Changes to how future external systems supply identifiers could reduce
> long-term reporting usefulness.

# 3.0 Supporting Documents 

## 3.1 As Is 

> Currently, users are unable to view the external source identifier
> directly within the KSB1 report grid. To access this information,
> users must navigate through multiple SAP reporting and document
> display screens to view document header data.
>
> This workflow requires repeated drill-down actions and is inefficient
> when reconciling large volumes of postings. The process increases
> reconciliation time and introduces opportunities for user error.
>
> Current workflow summary:

1.  Execute an SAP report group to access cost center reporting.

2.  Select a cost center and cost element.

3.  Navigate into individual line items.

4.  Open the associated financial document.

5.  View document header information to identify the external source
    system.

> This process is repetitive, time-consuming, and inefficient for
> high-volume reconciliation activities.

## 3.2 To Be 

> Users will be able to view the external source identifier directly
> within the KSB1 report output without navigating into individual
> document headers.
>
> With this improvement:

1.  Users access the KSB1 report.

2.  The report displays standard cost center line-item fields along with
    > the external source identifier.

3.  Reconciliation activities can be performed directly from the report
    > view.

> This change eliminates repetitive navigation into document headers,
> reduces reconciliation time for high-volume postings, and improves
> transparency of financial data.
>
> *Note: Screenshots and system visuals have been removed from this
> anonymized version.*

