## 4.3 Stakeholder Requirements 

> Business stakeholders require direct visibility into external source
> system identifiers within cost center line-item reporting to:

-   Efficiently reconcile financial postings

-   Reduce repetitive navigation into document headers

-   Identify posting sources without manual investigation

-   Increase confidence in reported financial data

## 4.4 solution Requirements 

> The solution must leverage existing SAP data elements and reporting
> capabilities to surface the external source identifier within the KSB1
> report.
>
> No new external data sources are required.

## 4.5 Non-Functional Requirements 

> The reporting enhancement must not introduce measurable performance
> degradation.
>
> Report execution time must remain consistent with current baseline
> behavior. The enhancement must not disrupt existing user workflows.

## 4.6 Transition Requirements 

> The enhancement must be deployed without requiring user retraining.
>
> Existing report variants and saved layouts must remain functional. No
> data migration is required.

## 4.7 Usability Requirements 

> The external source identifier must be clearly labeled and readable
> within the report.
>
> Field placement must align with existing reporting conventions.
>
> The report must remain usable for high-volume reconciliation
> activities.

## 4.8 Performance Requirements 

> The addition of the external source identifier must not increase
> report execution time beyond acceptable thresholds The report must
> continue to support high-volume data sets without degradation.

## 4.9 Supportability Requirements 

> The solution must be supportable using existing SAP support processes.
>
> No new monitoring or support tooling is required.
>
> Errors or inconsistencies in source identifiers must be traceable
> through existing support workflows.

## 4.10 Security Requirements 

> Access to the external source identifier must respect existing SAP
> authorization roles.
>
> Users without authorization to view cost center line items must not
> gain access through this enhancement.

## 4.11 Interface Requirements 

> The improvement must remain compatible with downstream reporting,
> exports, and integrations No changes to inbound or outbound interfaces
> are required.

## 4.12 Compliance Requirements 

> The solution must comply with existing financial reporting and audit
> requirements.
>
> The enhancement must not expose restricted or sensitive data beyond
> authorized users.

